The paper deals with predicting the quality of experience (QoE) in video streaming services, which involves analyzing sequential data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Multimedia (cs.MM), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Among these, cs.MM and cs.LG are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with multimedia data and machine learning models for QoE prediction. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that cs.CV is a likely category, while the focus on sequential data and time-series modeling could make cs.IR and cs.NE relevant as well.
